ith wry wit and considerable candor, Kuczynski’s story offers a fascinating perspective on the rise and fall of East Germany.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAuthors, GermanxBiographyx20th century. 0aAuthors, Germany20th centuryvBiography. 0aElite (Social sciences)xGermany (East). 0aElite (Social sciences)zGermany (East). 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Personal Memoirs.2bisacsh1 aKuczynski, Rita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteinhoff, Anthony J.1 aSteinhoff, Anthony J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144261635640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442616356423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442616356.jpg  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles